# Day 3 - DDL Commands

## Topics Covered
- CREATE
- ALTER
- TRUNCATE
- DROP

## What I Practiced

### CREATE
Creating tables with different data types.

### ALTER
Adding, modifying, and deleting columns.

### TRUNCATE
Removing all records while keeping the table structure.

### DROP
Deleting tables permanently.

## Key Takeaway
DDL (Data Definition Language) commands are used to define and manage the structure of database objects.

## Commands Practiced
- CREATE TABLE
- ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN
- ALTER TABLE MODIFY COLUMN
- ALTER TABLE DROP COLUMN
- TRUNCATE TABLE
- DROP TABLE
